COMMANDS.LABEL: 0x170
STRING: [Phorni] “Are you going to be home early today?”

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0x186
STRING: [Chris] “I guess so. Fal has to start work again today.”

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0x1b8
STRING: [Phorni] “She couldn't get the day off?”

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0x1ce
STRING: [Chris] “Seems that way.”

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0x200
STRING: [Phorni] “So that's why you're up early.”

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0x216
STRING: [Chris] “That's right. My private lessons with Ms. Cordell
are finally over now, but I really wasn't expecting I'd still
have to go to school in the mornings.”

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0x25c
STRING: [Phorni] “You look pretty happy despite that.”

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0x272
STRING: [Chris] “You might be right...”

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0x2a4
STRING: [Phorni] “You don't even deny it.”

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0x2ba
STRING: [Chris] “I wonder if you'll be able to understand this. I
like her on a human level of course, but also in terms of
music there's something special about her, so I can't
help it if I'm a bit excited.”

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0x300
STRING: [Phorni] “All sounds a little self-serving to me.”

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0x316
STRING: [Chris] “You're right... It is self-serving. But, the way she
sings has changed a little.”

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0x352
STRING: [Phorni] “Is that something that can actually change so
suddenly?”

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0x368
STRING: [Chris] “It could be because whatever it was that she
lacked, wasn't something to do with technique or
ability.”

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0x390
STRING: [Phorni] “...And now, you find her even more special?”

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0x3a6
STRING: [Chris] “I guess so.”

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0x3d8
STRING: [Phorni] “And you don't feel bad about this?”

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0x3ee
STRING: [Chris] “...I do. But, at the same time I feel that this is
right, too.”

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0x42a
STRING: [Phorni] “Oh... Then I guess there's nothing else for me
to say.”

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0x44a
STRING: [Chris] “Sorry.”

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0x47c
STRING: [Phorni] “Why apologize? It was written in that letter
from Arie, wasn't it? To do what you thought was right?

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0x49c
STRING: [Chris] “...Yeah.”

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0x4ce
STRING: [Phorni] “In that case, practice a lot and do your best to
put on a good recital.”

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0x4ee
STRING: [Chris] “Alright.”

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0x50c
STRING: [Phorni] “Good boy.

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0x53a
STRING: Okay then, see you later.”

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0x58a
STRING: There are times when I can't understand the way this
relationship between Phorni and me works.

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0x5a0
STRING: The moment we met, it felt like we were “owner and
pet.”

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0x5b6
STRING: Phorni couldn't do anything by herself, but it wasn't that
she needed anything either.

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0x5cc
STRING: However, she always needed my assistance when she
wanted to go outside.

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0x5e2
STRING: Because of this, I always thought of Phorni as a high
maintenance housemate.

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0x5f8
STRING: But she was probably the one supporting me mentally.

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0x604
STRING: Talking to Phorni about things that I had already gone
and made a decision on, just like earlier today, helped
me a lot, as she would always be supportive of me.

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0x624
STRING: There were things that I couldn't say to Torta or Asino,
but could say to Phorni.

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0x63a
STRING: Since I couldn't get responses from Arie immediately, I
needed something that I could turn to.

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0x6d6
STRING: After navigating the surprisingly crowded hallway and
then entering our practice room, I saw that Fal was
sitting down as she had already finished getting ready.

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0x6f6
STRING: [Chris] “Morning.”

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0x730
STRING: [Fal] “Yes, good morning. So getting straight down to
business...”

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0x746
STRING: [Chris] “Gah, that really is getting straight to it.”

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0x764
STRING: [Fal] “...I spoke to Ms. Cordell just before, she's going to
check our rehearsals after lunch.”

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0x784
STRING: [Chris] “What are we going to do until then?”

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0x7b6
STRING: [Fal] “We're going to practice, of course.

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0x7e4
STRING: I want to warm up too, I'm too scared to just suddenly
go and rehearse in front of her.”

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0x804
STRING: [Chris] “You saying that makes me start to feel
nervous...”

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0x836
STRING: [Fal] “It will be good practice for our recital.”

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0x84c
STRING: [Chris] “...Okay.”

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0x87e
STRING: [Fal] “Alright then, open up to the first page of the
score.”

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0x894
STRING: I felt relieved at how Fal seemed to be free of the
fatigue she felt yesterday.

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0x8aa
STRING: Of course I was worried about her physical state, but I
was also concerned about the words she said
yesterday. However, it seemed that she was back to the
usual old Fal.

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0x8f4
STRING: We ate the packed lunches that Fal made, and then
went to the classroom in which Ms. Cordell was waiting
for us.

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0x9b4
STRING: [Cordell] “You're right on time.”

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0x9e6
STRING: [Fal] “Thank you for offering to check our rehearsal.”

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0x9fc
STRING: [Chris] “We really appreciate it.”

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0xa1a
STRING: [Cordell] “Not a problem. You said you would practice
this morning, so I assume you don't need to warm up?”

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0xa42
STRING: [Fal] “That's right.”

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0xa60
STRING: [Cordell] “This will be my first time to hear the two of
you play, I am quite looking forward to it.”

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0xa80
STRING: [Chris] “...I'd prefer it if you didn't have too high
expectations, though.”

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0xab2
STRING: [Fal] “We'll be fine. Just play like you usually do.”

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0xac8
STRING: [Chris] “Yeah, you're right.”

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0xafa
STRING: [Cordell] “It seems you're confident, despite how you
sound.”

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0xb10
STRING: [Chris] “Well, we have been practicing now and then.”

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0xb42
STRING: [Fal] “A lot more than now and then.”

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0xb74
STRING: [Cordell] “Understood. In any case, let's hear it.”

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0xb8a
STRING: [Chris] “Yes, Ms. Cordell.”

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0xba2
STRING: I finished setting up, placed my fingers on the keyboard
of my Fortelle, and played the first note.

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0xc36
STRING: We finished our song, and the final sounds of Fal's voice
and my Fortelle disappeared into the sound proof walls.

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0xc68
STRING: [Cordell] “...Good.”

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0xc7e
STRING: Ms. Cordell gave her evaluation with a satisfied look on
her face.

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0xca6
STRING: [Fal] “Phew...”

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0xcbc
STRING: [Chris] “That's pretty much it.”

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0xcd2
STRING: No one in the room needed to give an opinion about
the quality of our music, we all understood quite well.

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0xce8
STRING: However, that change in Fal's voice that I noticed
yesterday, seemed to have reverted to how it was
before.

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0xcfe
STRING: It was something small and delicate, a special thing that
perhaps no one else besides Phorni and I would notice.

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0xd1e
STRING: Or, it was possible that no such thing even existed.

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0xd2a
STRING: Looking at the expression on Ms. Cordell's face, I almost
felt that it might have been nothing more than my
imagination.

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0xd40
STRING: Being able to gather this from Ms. Cordell's otherwise
unemotional expression, was something that was only
possible for the students like me who took private
lessons with her.

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0xd7c
STRING: [Cordell] “To be honest when I heard that you were
partnering up with Falsita, I had felt some concern, but
it seems that your compatibility wasn't so bad after all.”

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0xdb8
STRING: [Fal] “Compatibility?”

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0xdd6
STRING: [Cordell] “The combination of one student who is highly
dedicated and one who isn't. I believe there's more than
enough cause for concern there.”

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0xdf6
STRING: [Chris] “Is that...praise?”

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0xe28
STRING: [Cordell] “Did I not say it wasn't so bad?”

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0xe5a
STRING: [Fal] “Not bad...you say.”

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0xe70
STRING: [Chris] “Coming from Ms. Cordell, that's actually quite
the serving of praise. Normally, even if you did a good
job she'd just tell you to do it again, and that was it.”

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0xeac
STRING: [Fal] “Oh, I see.”

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0xede
STRING: [Cordell] “I can hear you, you know... But, I suppose
you're not trying to hide it from me.”

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0xf12
STRING: [Chris] “I don't think we could hide anything in such a
small room.”

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0xf30
STRING: [Cordell] “Fine. There is not much time left until the
recital, so keep practicing as you have been.”

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0xf50
STRING: [Chris] “Yes, Miss.”

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0xf6e
STRING: [Fal] “Yes, Miss.”

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0xfa2
STRING: We finished our song, and the final sounds of Fal's voice
and my Fortelle disappeared into the sound proof walls.

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0xfd4
STRING: [Cordell] “...Okay, that's enough.”

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0xfea
STRING: Ms. Cordell's facial expression was the same as always.

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0xff6
STRING: [Chris] “Something...didn't quite feel right.”

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0x1028
STRING: [Fal] “Yes. Were you nervous?”

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0x103e
STRING: Needless to say I had been nervous, but more so than
that, there had been something bothering me.

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0x1054
STRING: It felt as if the change I had noticed in Fal's voice
yesterday, had reverted to how it was before.

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0x106a
STRING: It was something small and delicate, a special thing that
perhaps no one else besides Phorni and I would notice.

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0x108a
STRING: Or, it was possible that no such thing even existed.

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0x1096
STRING: But... It had bothered me, and I wasn't able to put on a
satisfactory performance.

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0x10ac
STRING: I could tell by the expression on Ms. Cordell's face, just
what she had thought of our rehearsal.

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0x10b8
STRING: Being able to gather this from Ms. Cordell's otherwise
unemotional expression, was something that was only
possible for the students like me who took private
lessons with her.

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0x10f4
STRING: [Cordell] “If how you played just now wasn't your
usually quality, then there will be no problem. Just make
sure to get it right during the actual recital.”

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0x1130
STRING: [Fal] “We'll be okay, right, Chris?”

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0x1146
STRING: [Chris] “Yes, definitely.”

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0x1178
STRING: [Cordell] “I see... Since you both say it with such
confidence, I guess I have no choice but to believe you.”

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0x1198
STRING: [Chris] “It'll be okay.”

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0x11ae
STRING: I said it not only to Ms. Cordell and Fal, but also to
myself for self assurance.

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0x11e0
STRING: [Cordell] “There is not that much time left until the
recitals. Make sure to practice hard, and produce good
results.”

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0x1200
STRING: [Chris] “...That's surprising to hear from you, Ms.
Cordell.”

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0x121e
STRING: [Cordell] “If it were only you, Chris, I would have been
happy to say what I usually say.”

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0x1250
STRING: [Fal] “What you usually say?”

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0x126e
STRING: [Cordell] “To do as you please.”

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0x1284
STRING: [Chris] “Whether the results are good or bad, everything
will come back to me eventually, right?”

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0x12ac
STRING: [Cordell] “Exactly. What those around you deem as a
good result may actually not mean a good result for
you.”

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0x12e8
STRING: [Fal] “...That can actually happen?”

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0x1306
STRING: [Cordell] “It might.

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0x1334
STRING: However, it's also possible that it might not.”

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0x134a
STRING: Ms. Cordell let out a rare laugh.

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0x1356
STRING: Now that I thought about it, I had the feeling that Ms.
Cordell always talked about those kind of things.

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0x136c
STRING: There was the side of her that taught the technicalities
of music, but there was the emotional part of her that
always left everything in the hands of the student.

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0x1382
STRING: She always made a student practice until they could get
it right, but never criticized them when they couldn't.

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0x1398
STRING: And if the student started to become impatient, or if she
felt nothing would come from having them practice
more, she would give them a proper break.

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0x13ae
STRING: It wasn't an over exaggeration to say that the only
reason a student like me has been able to get this far,
was because I was placed under Ms. Cordell.

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0x13c4
STRING: “Do as you please.”

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0x13d0
STRING: Those words, were almost in alignment with what Arie
had written in her letter.

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0x13dc
STRING: I felt like I may have been blessed.

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0x1404
STRING: [Cordell] “To be honest, when I heard that you were
partnering up with Falsita, I had felt some concern, but
in any case it seems that your compatibility wasn't so
bad after all.”

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0x1440
STRING: [Fal] “Compatibility?”

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0x1472
STRING: [Cordell] “The combination of one student who is highly
dedicated, and one who isn't especially. I believe there's
more than enough cause for concern there.”

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0x1492
STRING: [Chris] “...I guess if it's not bad, that means it must be
good.”

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0x14ba
STRING: [Cordell] “Interpret it however you please.”

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0x1502
STRING: [Cordell] “Anyway. There is not that much time left until
the recitals. No slacking off.”

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0x1536
STRING: [Chris] “Yes, Miss.”

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0x1554
STRING: [Fal] “Yes, Miss.”

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0x156c
STRING: We had concluded our business.

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0x1578
STRING: Ms. Cordell was a busy person, so I packed up quickly
and went to leave.

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0x158e
STRING: I slung my Fortelle over my shoulder, and when I
reached towards the door, Ms. Cordell asked me
something, as if she had just remembered to do so.

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0x15c0
STRING: [Cordell] “Have you heard anything from Asino about his
partner?”

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0x15e0
STRING: [Chris] “Huh? No, nothing in particular. I know he is
looking, though.”

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0x1608
STRING: [Cordell] “I see... That is fine, then.”

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0x161e
STRING: [Chris] “If I see him, shall I tell him you'd like to see him?

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0x165a
STRING: [Cordell] “No. I'll let him decide in regard to his partner,
and whether or not he would like to tell me.”

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0x167a
STRING: [Chris] “...Are you sure?”

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0x16ac
STRING: [Cordell] “My biggest cause for concern seems to be on
top of things. I am sure Asino will be fine, too.”

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0x16cc
STRING: [Chris] “Cause for concern... Do you mean me?”

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0x16fe
STRING: [Cordell] “Yes.”

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0x1730
STRING: [Fal] “Hehe...”

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0x1746
STRING: Seeing Ms. Cordell answer my question with a smile on
her face, Fal laughed a little.

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0x175c
STRING: I considered saying something back, but I didn't have
the energy.

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0x1772
STRING: I simply grimaced, and left the classroom.

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0x17d6
STRING: [Fal] “I didn't know Ms. Cordell could laugh like that.”

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0x17ec
STRING: [Chris] “...It only happens on rare occasions.”

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0x180a
STRING: [Fal] “My impression of her has changed a little. It
seems like she really cares about you. She must have
taken a liking to you.”

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0x182a
STRING: [Chris] “I guess you could be right... You know what
they say about teachers having soft spots for their worst
students.”

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0x1852
STRING: [Fal] “It's very much like you to say something like that
about yourself, isn't it, Chris?”

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0x1868
STRING: [Chris] “Again... I'm not entirely sure if you're
complimenting me or not.”

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0x189a
STRING: [Fal] “It's more or less a compliment.

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0x18c8
STRING: I wouldn't say something like that unless I liked the
person.”

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0x18de
STRING: Fal said this with a smile on her face.

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0x18ea
STRING: Of course... It was fair to assume that she meant like, as
in friends.

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0x1900
STRING: [Chris] “Well... Thanks.”

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0x1932
STRING: [Fal] “Okay, I guess that's it for today.”

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0x1948
STRING: [Chris] “You've got work next?”

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0x1966
STRING: [Fal] “Yes.”

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0x197c
STRING: [Chris] “I see. So, in the end you're working everyday
until graduation?”

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0x199a
STRING: [Fal] “The graduation ceremony is in February, and after
that I will be moving out of my apartment, so... I guess
I'll be working until then.”

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0x19ba
STRING: [Chris] “So either way, you've got no off days until the
recital, huh?”

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0x19ec
STRING: [Fal] “It goes without saying that I'll have that day off, of
course.”

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0x1a02
STRING: Saying this with a grimace on her face, Fal then broke
into a smile.

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0x1a0e
STRING: It was a smile that betrayed no fatigue, and no
hesitation.

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0x1a1a
STRING: [Chris] “Let's do our best.”

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0x1a30
STRING: That was the only thing I could say.

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0x1a3c
STRING: Furthermore, the things we could do at this point were
limited too.

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0x1a48
STRING: So, I promised myself deep down that the one thing I
would do, was my best.

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0x1a70
STRING: [Fal] “...Yes, we'll do just that.”

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0x1a86
STRING: Fal nodded strongly, as if gathering her determination.

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0x1acc
STRING: Night soon came, and I was in the mood to eat out, and
this was the first place that came to mind.

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0x1ae2
STRING: And on top of that, it was almost about time for Fal to
finish her shift.

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0x1aee
STRING: We hadn't made any plans to meet, but thinking that
just maybe it would be possible, I entered the trattoria.

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0x1b2c
STRING: I was guided to a two person table, and some moments
later, a familiar looking server came to take my order.

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0x1b4a
STRING: [Clerk] “Are you ready to order?”

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0x1b60
STRING: [Chris] “Ah, yes.”

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0x1b76
STRING: I ordered the first thing on the menu the stood out to
me.

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0x1b8c
STRING: I considered asking about Fal while I was at it, but I
decided not to, thinking that it might be a bit
shameless.

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0x1ba2
STRING: After that, I ate my meal while being somewhat
preoccupied with the kitchen, but in the end I didn't get
to see Fal.

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0x1bb8
STRING: However, the meal was delicious as usual, so I had
nothing to be unhappy about.

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0x1c08
STRING: I peeked into the kitchen one last time, and then went
back to my apartment.
